Carolyn D. Wright was born in Mountain Home, Arkansas and educated at Memphis State College (now the University of Memphis) and at the University of Arkansas. She has published numerous volumes of poetry, including: 
               Translation of the Gospel Back into Tongues
             (1981); 
               Further Adventures with You
             (1986); 
               String Light
            (1991), which won the Poetry Center Book Award; 
               Tremble
             (1996); 
               Deepstep Come Shining
             (1998); 
               Steal Away: New and Selected Poems
             (2002); 
               One Big Self: Prisoners of Louisiana
             (2003), with photographer Deborah Luster; 
               Cooling Time: An American Poetry Vigil
             (2005); and 
               Rising, Falling, Hovering
             (2008), which won the Griffin Poetry Prize.
